This paper involves the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques for predicting chemical compounds, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence and machine learning. The use of SMILES representation and beam search also suggests a focus on natural language processing and language generation, which falls under the domain of computational linguistics. The paper also involves the analysis of data memorization and generalization performance, which suggests a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
